OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FArizona to ban people      
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ffilming police officers    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fwithin 8 feet              
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A law in the US state of Arizona will  
OL,6, ban people from filming police officers
OL,7, at short distances, with possible fines
OL,8, or jail for those who don't comply.    
OL,10,FCritics call the law a threat to free  
OL,11,Fspeech and the right to a free press.  
OL,13,FPolice are often filmed by bystanders  
OL,14,Fand footage has occasionally resulted  
OL,15,Fin officer misconduct being exposed.   
OL,17,FThe law comes into effect on 24        
OL,18,FSeptember and will make it illegal to  
OL,19,Ffilm police officers in the state      
OL,20,Fwithin a distance of 8 feet (2.4m).    
